Island Information, PAL Holdings: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-23T00:31:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/island-information-pal-holdings-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.3 percent to
3,854.14.  Island Information & Technology Inc. (IS)  : The company
that invests in Internet technology and global  computer networks 
has been authorized by its board to hold a stock rights
offering, an exchange filing showed. The stock was unchanged at
4.8 centavos.  PAL Holdings Inc. (PAL)  : The ground crew of Philippine
Airlines Inc., the nation’s largest carrier and a unit of PAL,
will start voting today on whether to go on strike to protest
management’s refusal to “bargain” with the group, Philippine
Airlines Employees Association President Gerry Rivera said.
Results of the vote may be known March 25, he said. The stock
was unchanged at 4.90 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  